<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE of 10 June 1991 on prevention of the use of the financial system for the purpose of money laundering (91/308/EEC) </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV rahanduss&uuml;steemi rahapesu eesm&auml;rgil kasutamise v&auml;ltimise kohta 10. juuni 1991 (91/308/EM&Uuml;) </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 57 (2), first and third sentences, and Article 100a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 57 l&otilde;ike 2 esimest ja kolmandat lauset ning artiklit 100a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> In cooperation with the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> koost&ouml;&ouml;s Euroopa Parlamendiga, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas when credit and financial institutions are used to launder proceeds from criminal activities (hereinafter referred to as 'money laundering'), the soundness and stability of the institution concerned and confidence in the financial system as a whole could be seriously jeopardized, thereby losing the trust of the public; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutuste kasutamine kuritegelikul teel saadud tulu rahapesuks (edaspidi "rahapesu") v&otilde;ib t&otilde;siselt ohustada asjaomase asutuse usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsust ja stabiilsust ning usaldust rahanduss&uuml;steemi vastu &uuml;ldiselt, nii et need kaotavad &uuml;ldsuse usalduse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas lack of Community action against money laundering could lead Member States, for the purpose of protecting their financial systems, to adopt measures which could be inconsistent with completion of the single market; whereas, in order to facilitate their criminal activities, launderers could try to take advantage of the freedom of capital movement and freedom to supply financial services which the integrated financial area involves, if certain coordinating measures are not adopted at Community level; </inglise>
<eesti> kuna &uuml;hendusel puuduvad rahapesuvastased meetmed, v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid oma rahanduss&uuml;steemide kaitseks vastu v&otilde;tta meetmed, mis v&otilde;ivad olla vastuolus siseturu v&auml;ljakujundamisega; kui &uuml;henduse tasandil ei v&otilde;eta vastu teatavaid koosk&otilde;lastusmeetmeid, v&otilde;idakse rahapesuga p&uuml;&uuml;da kuritegeliku tegevuse h&otilde;lbustamiseks &auml;ra kasutada &uuml;htse finantspiirkonnaga kaasnevat kapitali liikumise ja finantsteenuste osutamise vabadust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas money laundering has an evident influence on the rise of organized crime in general and drug trafficking in particular; whereas there is more and more awareness that combating money laundering is one of the most effective means of opposing this form of criminal activity, which constitutes a particular threat to Member States' societies; </inglise>
<eesti> rahapesu avaldab ilmset m&otilde;ju organiseeritud kuritegevuse kasvule &uuml;ldiselt ning eelk&otilde;ige uimasti&auml;ri kasvule; &uuml;ldsus muutub &uuml;ha teadlikumaks sellest, et rahapesu t&otilde;kestamine on &uuml;ks t&otilde;husamaid viise v&otilde;itlemisel k&otilde;nealuse kuritegeliku tegevuse vastu, mis kujutab liikmesriikide &uuml;hiskondlikule korraldusele eriti suurt ohtu; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas money laundering must be combated mainly by penal means and within the framework of international cooperation among judicial and law enforcement authorities, as has been undertaken, in the field of drugs, by the United Nations Convention Against Illicit Traffic in Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances, adopted on 19 December 1988 in Vienna (hereinafter referred to as the 'Vienna Convention') and more generally in relation to all criminal activities, by the Council of Europe Convention on laundering, tracing, seizure and confiscation of proceeds of crime, opened for signature on 8 November 1990 in Strasbourg; </inglise>
<eesti> rahapesu tuleb t&otilde;kestada peamiselt kriminaal&otilde;igusmeetmete kaudu ning kohtute ja &otilde;iguskaitseasutuste rahvusvahelise koost&ouml;&ouml; raames, mida on tehtud uimasti&auml;ri valdkonnas vastavalt Viinis 19. detsembril 1988 vastu v&otilde;etud narkootiliste ja ps&uuml;hhotroopsete ainete ebaseadusliku ringluse vastasele &Uuml;RO konventsioonile (edaspidi "Viini konventsioon") ning muu kuritegeliku tegevusega seoses vastavalt Euroopa N&otilde;ukogu rahapesu ning kriminaaltulu avastamise, arestimise ja konfiskeerimise konventsioonile, mis avati allakirjutamiseks Strasbourgis 8. novembril 1990; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas a penal approach should, however, not be the only way to combat money laundering, since the financial system can play a highly effective role; whereas reference must be made in this context to the recommendation of the Council of Europe of 27 June 1980 and to the declaration of principles adopted in December 1988 in Basle by the banking supervisory authorities of the Group of Ten, both of which constitute major steps towards preventing the use of the financial system for money laundering; </inglise>
<eesti> kriminaal&otilde;iguslik l&auml;henemine ei peaks olema ainus viis rahapesu t&otilde;kestamiseks, sest ka rahanduss&uuml;steemi tugevdamine v&otilde;ib olla v&auml;ga t&otilde;hus vahend; sellega seoses tuleb viidata Euroopa N&otilde;ukogu 27. juuni 1980. aasta soovitusele ning Baselis 1998. aasta detsembris k&uuml;mne grupi riikide pankade j&auml;relevalveasutuste poolt vastu v&otilde;etud p&otilde;him&otilde;tete deklaratsioonile, mis on m&otilde;lemad oluliseks sammuks rahanduss&uuml;steemi rahapesu eesm&auml;rgil kasutamise v&auml;ltimise suunas; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas money laundering is usually carried out in an international context so that the criminal origin of the funds can be better disguised; whereas measures exclusively adopted at a national level, without taking account of international coordination and cooperation, would have very limited effects; </inglise>
<eesti> rahapesu toimub tavaliselt rahvusvahelisel tasandil, sest sel viisil saab paremini varjata rahaliste vahendite kriminaalset p&auml;ritolu; &uuml;ksnes siseriiklikul tasandil vastu v&otilde;etavatel meetmetel, milles ei peeta silmas rahvusvahelist koosk&otilde;lastamist ja koost&ouml;&ouml;d, oleks v&auml;ga piiratud m&otilde;ju; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas any measures adopted by the Community in this field should be consistent with other action undertaken in other international fora; whereas in this respect any Community action should take particular account of the recommendations adopted by the financial action task force on money laundering, set up in July 1989 by the Paris summit of the seven most developed countries; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;ik &uuml;henduse poolt k&auml;esolevas valdkonnas vastu v&otilde;etavad meetmed peavad olema koosk&otilde;las muude rahvusvahelistel foorumidel v&otilde;etavate meetmetega; seet&otilde;ttu tuleb k&otilde;igi &uuml;henduse meetmete puhul eriti arvesse v&otilde;tta 1989. aasta juulis seitsme juhtiva t&ouml;&ouml;stusriigi Pariisi tippkohtumisel loodud rahapesuvastase t&ouml;&ouml;konna soovitusi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the European Parliament has requested, in several resolutions, the establishment of a global Community programme to combat drug trafficking, including provisions on prevention of money laundering; </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa Parlament on mitmes resolutsioonis taotlenud laiaulatusliku uimasti&auml;ri t&otilde;kestava &uuml;henduse tegevusprogrammi koostamist, mis sisaldaks ka rahapesu v&auml;ltimist k&auml;sitlevaid s&auml;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas for the purposes of this Directive the definition of money laundering is taken from that adopted in the Vienna Convention; whereas, however, since money laundering occurs not only in relation to the proceeds of drug-related offences but also in relation to the proceeds of other criminal activities (such as organized crime and terrorism), the Member States should, within the meaning of their legislation, extend the effects of the Directive to include the proceeds of such activities, to the extent that they are likely to result in laundering operations justifying sanctions on that basis; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamisel l&auml;htutakse Viini konventsioonis esitatud rahapesu m&auml;&auml;ratlusest; kuna rahapesu ei ole seotud mitte ainult uimastikuritegevusest saadava tuluga, vaid ka muul kuritegelikul teel saadava tuluga (n&auml;iteks organiseeritud kuritegevus ja terrorism), peaksid liikmesriigid oma &otilde;igusaktides laiendama k&auml;esoleva direktiivi toimet ka muul kuritegelikul teel saadava tulu suhtes vastavalt sellele, kui t&otilde;en&auml;oline on, et see v&otilde;ib olla seotud rahapesuga, mille korral on p&otilde;hjendatud sanktsioonide rakendamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas prohibition of money laundering in Member States' legislation backed by appropriate measures and penalties is a necessary condition for combating this phenomenon; </inglise>
<eesti> rahapesu keelustamine liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktides koos asjakohaste meetmete ja karistustega on vajalikud eeltingimused selle n&auml;htusega v&otilde;itlemiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas ensuring that credit and financial institutions require identification of their customers when entering into business relations or conducting transactions, exceeding certain thresholds, are necessary to avoid launderers' taking advantage of anonymity to carry out their criminal activities; whereas such provisions must also be extended, as far as possible, to any beneficial owners; </inglise>
<eesti> selleks, et rahapesuga ei saaks anon&uuml;&uuml;msust &auml;ra kasutades toime panna kuritegusid, peavad krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused n&otilde;udma &auml;risuhete loomisel ning teatavaid piirm&auml;&auml;rasid &uuml;letavate tehingute sooritamisel kliendi isikusamasuse tuvastamist; neid s&auml;tteid tuleks v&otilde;imaluse korral laiendada k&otilde;igile tulusaavatele omanikele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas credit and financial institutions must keep for at least five years copies or references of the identification documents required as well as supporting evidence and records consisting of documents relating to transactions or copies thereof similarly admissible in court proceedings under the applicable national legislation for use as evidence in any investigation into money laundering; </inglise>
<eesti> krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused peavad v&auml;hemalt viis aastat s&auml;ilitama n&otilde;utavate isikut t&otilde;endavate dokumentide koopiaid v&otilde;i viiteid, t&otilde;endusmaterjale ning registreid, mis sisaldavad tehingutega seotud dokumente v&otilde;i nende koopiaid, mida v&otilde;ib riigi vastavate &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt kasutada kohtumenetluste k&auml;igus t&otilde;endusmaterjalina rahapesu uurimisel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas ensuring that credit and financial institutions examine with special attention any transaction which they regard as particularly likely, by its nature, to be related to money laundering is necessary in order to preserve the soundness and integrity of the financial system as well as to contribute to combating this phenomenon; whereas to this end they should pay special attention to transactions with third countries which do not apply comparable standards against money laundering to those established by the Community or to other equivalent standards set out by international fora and endorsed by the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> rahanduss&uuml;steemi usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsuse ja puutumatuse tagamiseks ning rahapesuga v&otilde;itlemiseks peavad krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused erilise t&auml;helepanuga l&auml;bi vaatama k&otilde;ik tehingud, mille puhul on nende laadi arvesse v&otilde;ttes eriti t&otilde;en&auml;oline, et need v&otilde;ivad olla seotud rahapesuga; seet&otilde;ttu peaksid nad p&ouml;&ouml;rama erilist t&auml;helepanu tehingutele kolmandate riikidega, kes ei kohalda rahapesu suhtes standardeid, mis on v&otilde;rreldavad &uuml;henduse kehtestatud standarditega v&otilde;i rahvusvahelistel foorumidel kehtestatud ja &uuml;henduse poolt kinnitatud muude samav&auml;&auml;rsete standarditega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for those purposes, Member States may ask credit and financial institutions to record in writing the results of the examination they are required to carry out and to ensure that those results are available to the authorities responsible for efforts to eliminate money laundering; </inglise>
<eesti> sellega seoses v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid n&otilde;uda, et krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused vormistaksid kirjalikult k&otilde;igi nendelt n&otilde;utavate uurimiste tulemused ning tagaksid, et need on k&auml;ttesaadavad rahapesu t&otilde;kestamise eest vastutavatele asutustele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas preventing the financial system from being used for money laundering is a task which cannot be carried out by the authorities responsible for combating this phenomenon without the cooperation of credit and financial institutions and their supervisory authorities; whereas banking secrecy must be lifted in such cases; whereas a mandatory system of reporting suspicious transactions which ensures that information is transmitted to the abovementioned authorities without alerting the customers concerned, is the most effective way to accomplish such cooperation; whereas a special protection clause is necessary to exempt credit and financial institutions, their employees and their directors from responsibility for breaching restrictions on disclosure of information; </inglise>
<eesti> rahanduss&uuml;steemi rahapesuks kasutamise v&auml;ltimine on &uuml;lesanne, mida selle eest vastutavad asutused ei saa t&auml;ita, tegemata koost&ouml;&ouml;d krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutuste ja nende j&auml;relevalveasutustega; sellistel juhtudel tuleb loobuda pangasaladusest; t&otilde;husaim viis k&otilde;nealuse koost&ouml;&ouml; tagamiseks on sisse seada kahtlastest tehingutest teatamise kohustuslik kord, mis tagab teabe edastamise eespool nimetatud asutustele asjaomaseid kliente teavitamata; on vaja erilist kaitseklauslit krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutuste ning nende t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja juhtide vabastamiseks teabe avalikustamisele kehtestatud piirangute rikkumisega kaasnevast vastutusest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the information received by the authorities pursuant to this Directive may be used only in connection with combating money laundering; whereas Member States may nevertheless provide that this information may be used for other purposes; </inglise>
<eesti> teavet, mida asutused saavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi alusel, v&otilde;ib kasutada ainult rahapesu t&otilde;kestamiseks; liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad siiski ette n&auml;ha, et k&otilde;nealust teavet v&otilde;ib kasutada ka muudel eesm&auml;rkidel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas establishment by credit and financial institutions of procedures of internal control and training programmes in this field are complementary provisions without which the other measures contained in this Directive could become ineffective; </inglise>
<eesti> krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutuste poolt k&otilde;nealuses valdkonnas ette n&auml;htud sisekontrolli kord ja koolitusprogrammid on t&auml;iendavad s&auml;tted, milleta teised k&auml;esolevas direktiivis s&auml;testatud meetmed v&otilde;ivad osutuda ebat&otilde;husaks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, since money laundering can be carried out not only through credit and financial institutions but also through other types of professions and categories of undertakings, Member States must extend the provisions of this Directive in whole or in part, to include those professions and undertakings whose activities are particularly likely to be used for money laundering purposes; </inglise>
<eesti> kuna rahapesuga saab lisaks krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutuste kaudu tegelda ka teisi kutsealasid ja muid ettev&otilde;ttekategooriaid kasutades, peavad liikmesriigid laiendama k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tteid osaliselt v&otilde;i t&auml;ielikult ka nendele kutsealadele ja ettev&otilde;tetele, kelle tegevust saab eriti t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt kasutada rahapesuks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is important that the Member States should take particular care to ensure that coordinated action is taken in the Community where there are strong grounds for believing that professions or activities the conditions governing the pursuit of which have been harmonized at Community level are being used for laundering money; </inglise>
<eesti> on t&auml;htis, et liikmesriigid p&uuml;&uuml;aksid tagada &uuml;henduse tasandil koosk&otilde;lastatud tegutsemist juhul, kui tekib p&otilde;hjendatud kahtlus, et rahapesu eesm&auml;rgil kasutatakse &uuml;henduse tasandil &uuml;htlustatult reguleeritud kutse- v&otilde;i tegevusalasid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the effectiveness of efforts to eliminate money laundering is particularly dependent on the close coordination and harmonization of national implementing measures; whereas such coordination and harmonization which is being carried out in various international bodies requires, in the Community context, cooperation between Member States and the Commission in the framework of a contact committee; </inglise>
<eesti> rahapesu t&otilde;kestamiseks v&otilde;etavate meetmete t&otilde;husus s&otilde;ltub eelk&otilde;ige siseriiklike rakendusmeetmete p&otilde;hjalikust koosk&otilde;lastamisest ja &uuml;htlustamisest; erinevates rahvusvahelistes organites toimuv koosk&otilde;lastamine ja &uuml;htlustamine n&otilde;uab &uuml;henduse tasandil liikmesriikide ja komisjoni tihedat koost&ouml;&ouml;d kontaktkomitees; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is for each Member State to adopt appropriate measures and to penalize infringement of such measures in an appropriate manner to ensure full application of this Directive, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva direktiivi t&auml;ieliku kohaldamise tagamiseks peab iga liikmesriik vastu v&otilde;tma asjakohased meetmed ja m&auml;&auml;rama nende meetmete rikkumise korral kohaldatava asjakohase karistuse, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> - 'credit institution' means a credit institution, as defined as in the first indent of Article 1 of Directive 77/780/EEC (4), as last amended by Directive 89/646/EEC (5), and includes branches within the meaning of the third indent of that Article and located in the Community, of credit institutions having their head offices outside the Community, </inglise>
<eesti> - krediidiasutus - n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 77/780/EM&Uuml; (4) (viimati muudetud direktiiviga 89/646/EM&Uuml; (5)) artikli 1 esimeses taandes m&auml;&auml;ratletud krediidiasutus, sealhulgas nimetatud artikli kolmandas taandes m&auml;&auml;ratletud selliste krediidiasutuste &uuml;henduses asuvad filiaalid, kelle peakontor asub v&auml;ljaspool &uuml;hendust, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'financial institution' means an undertaking other than a credit institution whose principal activity is to carry out one or more of the operations included in numbers 2 to 12 and number 14 of the list annexed to Directive 89/646/EEC, or an insurance company duly authorized in accordance with Directive 79/267/EEC (6), as last amended by Directive 90/619/EEC (7), in so far as it carries out activities covered by that Directive; this definition includes branches located in the Community of financial institutions whose head offices are outside the Community, </inglise>
<eesti> - finantseerimisasutus - ettev&otilde;te, v&auml;lja arvatud krediidiasutus, kelle p&otilde;hitegevus kuulub &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme direktiivile 89/646/EM&Uuml; lisatud loetelu punktides 2-12 ja punktis 14 nimetatud tegevusala hulka, v&otilde;i direktiiviga 79/267/EM&Uuml;, (6) viimati muudetud direktiiviga 90/619/EM&Uuml;, (7) koosk&otilde;las n&otilde;uetekohaselt volitatud kindlustusselts, mis tegutseb k&otilde;nealuse direktiiviga h&otilde;lmatud tegevusvaldkondades; see m&otilde;iste h&otilde;lmab v&auml;ljaspool &uuml;hendust peakontorit omavate finantseerimisasutuste &uuml;henduses asuvaid filiaale, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'money laundering' means the following conduct when committed intentionally: </inglise>
<eesti> - rahapesu - h&otilde;lmab j&auml;rgmist ettekavatsetud tegevust: </eesti>
<inglise> - the conversion or transfer of property, knowing that such property is derived from criminal activity or from an act of participation in such activity, for the purpose of concealing or disguising the illicit origin of the property or of assisting any person who is involved in the commission of such activity to evade the legal consequences of his action, </inglise>
<eesti> - vara muundamine v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmine, kui on teada, et niisugune vara on saadud kuriteo toimepanemisest v&otilde;i selles osalemisest, selleks et varjata v&otilde;i hoida saladuses vara ebaseaduslikku p&auml;ritolu v&otilde;i abistada isikut, kes osales kuriteo toimepanemises, et ta saaks hoiduda oma tegude &otilde;iguslikest tagaj&auml;rgedest; </eesti>
<inglise> - the concealment or disguise of the true nature, source, location, disposition, movement, rights with respect to, or ownership of property, knowing that such property is derived from criminal activity or from an act of participation in such activity, </inglise>
<eesti> - vara t&otilde;elise olemuse, p&auml;ritolu, asukoha, k&auml;sutamisviisi, &uuml;mberpaigutamise, omandi&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i muude varaga seotud &otilde;iguste varjamine v&otilde;i saladuses hoidmine, kui on teada, et niisugune vara on saadud kuriteo toimepanemisest v&otilde;i selles osalemisest; </eesti>
<inglise> - the acquisition, possession or use of property, knowing, at the time of receipt, that such property was derived from criminal activity or from an act of participation in such activity, </inglise>
<eesti> - vara omandamine, omamine v&otilde;i kasutamine, kui selle saamisel on teada, et selline vara on saadud kuriteo toimepanemisest v&otilde;i selles osalemisest; </eesti>
<inglise> - participation in, association to commit, attempts to commit and aiding, abetting, facilitating and counselling the commission of any of the actions mentioned in the foregoing paragraphs. </inglise>
<eesti> - kokkuleppes osalemine v&otilde;i sellega seotus eelnevates l&otilde;ikudes nimetatud tegude toimepanemiseks, nende toimepaneku katsed ning nendele kaasaaitamine ja kihutamine v&otilde;i nende soodustamine v&otilde;i nendeks n&otilde;uandmine. </eesti>
<inglise> Knowledge, intent or purpose required as an element of the abovementioned activities may be inferred from objective factual circumstances. </inglise>
<eesti> Teadmist, kavatsust v&otilde;i eesm&auml;rki, mis kuuluvad eespool nimetatud tegude koosseisu, v&otilde;ib tuletada teo objektiivsete tegelike asjaolude p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise> Money laundering shall be regarded as such even where the activities which generated the property to be laundered were perpetrated in the territory of another Member State or in that of a third country. </inglise>
<eesti> Rahapesuga on tegemist ka juhul, kui tegevus, mille tulemusel saadi rahapesus kasutatav vara, toimus m&otilde;ne teise liikmesriigi v&otilde;i kolmanda riigi territooriumil; </eesti>
<inglise> - 'Property' means assets of every kind, whether corporeal or incorporeal, movable or immovable, tangible or intangible, and legal documents or instruments evidencing title to or interests in such assets. </inglise>
<eesti> - vara - igasugune vara, nii kehaline kui kehatu, nii kinnis- kui vallasasi, nii materiaalne kui mittemateriaalne, samuti sellise vara omandi&otilde;igust v&otilde;i muid &otilde;igusi t&otilde;endavad juriidilised dokumendid v&otilde;i aktid; </eesti>
<inglise> - 'Criminal activity' means a crime specified in Article 3 (1) (a) of the Vienna Convention and any other criminal activity designated as such for the purposes of this Directive by each Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> - kuritegelik tegevus - Viini konventsiooni artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis a m&auml;&auml;ratletud kuritegu ja muu kuritegelik tegevus, mille liikmesriik on m&auml;&auml;ratlenud kuriteona k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> - 'Competent authorities' means the national authorities empowered by law or regulation to supervise credit or financial institutions. </inglise>
<eesti> - p&auml;devad asutused - liikmesriigi asutused, kelle p&auml;devusse on seadusega v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;rusega antud krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutuste j&auml;relevalve. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that money laundering as defined in this Directive is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad tagama k&auml;esolevas direktiivis m&auml;&auml;ratletud rahapesu keelustamise. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that credit and financial institutions require identification of their customers by means of supporting evidence when entering into business relations, particularly when opening an account or savings accounts, or when offering safe custody facilities. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad tagama, et krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused n&otilde;uavad &auml;risuhete loomisel ning eelk&otilde;ige kontode v&otilde;i hoiukontode avamisel v&otilde;i pangahoidla teenuste pakkumisel kliendi isikusamasuse tuvastamist t&otilde;endavate dokumentide alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The identification requirement shall also apply for any transaction with customers other than those referred to in paragraph 1, involving a sum amounting to ECU 15 000 or more, whether the transaction is carried out in a single operation or in several operations which seem to be linked. </inglise>
<eesti> Isikusamasuse tuvastamise n&otilde;uet kohaldatakse klientidega, v&auml;lja arvatud l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud kliendid, tehtavate k&otilde;ikide tehingute suhtes, mille v&auml;&auml;rtus on v&auml;hemalt 15 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;d, olenemata sellest, kas tehing on &uuml;hekordne v&otilde;i koosneb mitmest &uuml;ksteisega t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt seotud toimingust. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the sum is not known at the time when the transaction is undertaken, the institution concerned shall proceed with identification as soon as it is apprised of the sum and establishes that the threshold has been reached. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui tehingu tegemise ajal on selle v&auml;&auml;rtus teadmata, j&auml;tkab asjaomane asutus isikusamasuse tuvastamist kohe, kui ta on v&auml;&auml;rtuse teada saanud ja kindlaks teinud, et see &uuml;letab etten&auml;htud piirm&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> By way of derogation from paragraphs 1 and 2, the identification requirements with regard to insurance policies written by insurance undertakings within the meaning of Directive 79/267/EEC, where they perform activities which fall within the scope of that Directive shall not be required where the periodic premium amount or amounts to be paid in any given year does or do not exceed ECU 1 000 or where a single premium is paid amounting to ECU 2 500 or less. </inglise>
<eesti> Erandina l&otilde;igetest 1 ja 2 ei n&otilde;uta isikusamasuse tuvastamist direktiivis 79/267/EM&Uuml; m&auml;&auml;ratletud ja k&otilde;nealuse direktiiviga h&otilde;lmatud toimingutega tegelevate kindlustusseltside poolt v&auml;lja antud kindlustuspoliiside puhul, kui teatava aasta j&auml;rgpreemia v&otilde;i j&auml;rgpreemiad ei &uuml;leta 1000 ek&uuml;&uuml;d v&otilde;i kui &uuml;hekordne preemia ei &uuml;leta 2500 ek&uuml;&uuml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> If the periodic premium amount or amounts to be paid in any given year is or are increased so as to exceed the ECU 1 000 threshold, identification shall be required. </inglise>
<eesti> Isikusamasuse tuvastamist n&otilde;utakse juhul, kui teatava aasta j&auml;rgpreemiat v&otilde;i j&auml;rgpreemiaid suurendatakse nii, et need &uuml;letavad 1000 ek&uuml;&uuml; piirm&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may provide that the identification requirement is not compulsory for insurance policies in respect of pension schemes taken out by virtue of a contract of employment or the insured's occupation, provided that such policies contain no surrender clause and may not be used as collateral for a loan. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad ette n&auml;ha, et isikusamasuse tuvastamise n&otilde;ue ei ole kohustuslik t&ouml;&ouml;lepingul v&otilde;i kindlustatud isiku ametil p&otilde;hinevate pensioniskeemidega seotud kindlustuspoliiside puhul, tingimusel et sellised poliisid ei sisalda loobumisklauslit ja neid ei kasutata laenutagatisena. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> In the event of doubt as to whether the customers referred to in the above paragraphs are acting on their own behalf, or where it is certain that they are not acting on their own behalf, the credit and financial institutions shall take reasonable measures to obtain information as to the real identity of the persons on whose behalf those customers are acting. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui tekib kahtlus, kas eelmistes l&otilde;igetes osutatud kliendid tegutsevad enda nimel, v&otilde;i kui on kindel, et nad ei tegutse enda nimel, v&otilde;tavad krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused otstarbekohased meetmed selleks, et saada teavet nende isikute kohta, kelle nimel sellised kliendid tegutsevad. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> Credit and financial institutions shall carry out such identification, even where the amount of the transaction is lower than the threshold laid down, wherever there is suspicion of money laundering. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused kahtlustavad rahapesu, peavad nad sellised isikud tuvastama isegi juhul, kui tehingu v&auml;&auml;rtus on kehtestatud piirm&auml;&auml;rast v&auml;iksem. </eesti>
<inglise> 7. </inglise>
<eesti> 7. </eesti>
<inglise> Credit and financial institutions shall not be subject to the identification requirements provided for in this Article where the customer is also a credit or financial institution covered by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutustel ei pea t&auml;itma k&auml;esolevas artiklis s&auml;testatud isikusamasuse tuvastamise n&otilde;uet juhul, kui kliendiks on k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga h&otilde;lmatud krediidi- v&otilde;i finantseerimisasutus. </eesti>
<inglise> 8. </inglise>
<eesti> 8. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may provide that the identification requirements regarding transactions referred to in paragraphs 3 and 4 are fulfilled when it is established that the payment for the transaction is to be debited from an account opened in the customer's name with a credit institution subject to this Directive according to the requirements of paragraph 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad ette n&auml;ha, et l&otilde;igetes 3 ja 4 osutatud tehingute puhul on isikusamasuse tuvastamise n&otilde;ue t&auml;idetud juhul, kui selgub, et tehinguga seotud makse tehakse kontolt, mis on avatud kliendi nimel k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga h&otilde;lmatud krediidiasutuses vastavalt l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that credit and financial institutions keep the following for use as evidence in any investigation into money laundering: </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad tagama, et krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused s&auml;ilitavad rahapesuga seotud v&otilde;imalike juurdluste jaoks t&otilde;endusmaterjalina j&auml;rgmisi dokumente: </eesti>
<inglise> - in the case of identification, a copy or the references of the evidence required, for a period of at least five years after the relationship with their customer has ended, </inglise>
<eesti> - isikusamasuse tuvastamise puhul n&otilde;utavate t&otilde;endite koopiaid v&otilde;i viiteid v&auml;hemalt viie aasta jooksul p&auml;rast kliendisuhte l&otilde;ppu, </eesti>
<inglise> - in the case of transactions, the supporting evidence and records, consisting of the original documents or copies admissible in court proceedings under the applicable national legislation for a period of at least five years following execution of the transactions. </inglise>
<eesti> - tehingute puhul v&auml;hemalt viie aasta jooksul p&auml;rast nende sooritamist t&otilde;endusmaterjale ning registreid, mis sisaldavad originaaldokumente v&otilde;i nende koopiaid, mida v&otilde;ib riigi vastavate &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt kasutada kohtumenetluste k&auml;igus. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that credit and financial institutions examine with special attention any transaction which they regard as particularly likely, by its nature, to be related to money laundering. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad tagama, et krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused vaatavad erilise t&auml;helepanuga l&auml;bi k&otilde;ik tehingud, mille puhul on nende laadi arvesse v&otilde;ttes eriti t&otilde;en&auml;oline, et need v&otilde;ivad olla seotud rahapesuga. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that credit and financial institutions and their directors and employees cooperate fully with the authorities responsible for combating money laundering: </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad tagama, et krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused ning nende juhid ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajad teevad tihedat koost&ouml;&ouml;d rahapesu t&otilde;kestamise eest vastutavate asutustega: </eesti>
<inglise> - by informing those authorities, on their own initiative, of any fact which might be an indication of money laundering, </inglise>
<eesti> - teavitades neid asutusi omal algatusel k&otilde;igist v&otilde;imalikule rahapesule viitavatest asjaoludest, </eesti>
<inglise> - by furnishing those authorities, at their request, with all necessary information, in accordance with the procedures established by the applicable legislation. </inglise>
<eesti> - esitades nende asutuste taotluse korral neile kogu vajaliku teabe kohaldatavates &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> The information referred to in the first paragraph shall be forwarded to the authorities responsible for combating money laundering of the Member State in whose territory the institution forwarding the information is situated. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimeses l&otilde;igus osutatud teave edastatakse rahapesu t&otilde;kestamise eest vastutavatele asutustele selles liikmesriigis, kelle territooriumil teavet edastav asutus paikneb. </eesti>
<inglise> The person or persons designated by the credit and financial institutions in accordance with the procedures provided for in Article 11 (1) shall normally forward the information. </inglise>
<eesti> Teavet edastavad tavaliselt krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutuste poolt artikli 11 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud korras selleks m&auml;&auml;ratud isikud. </eesti>
<inglise> Information supplied to the authorities in accordance with the first paragraph may be used only in connection with the combating of money laundering. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;devatele asutustele esimese l&otilde;igu kohaselt esitatud teavet v&otilde;ib kasutada ainult rahapesu t&otilde;kestamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> However, Member States may provide that such information may also be used for other purposes. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad siiski ette n&auml;ha, et k&otilde;nealust teavet v&otilde;ib kasutada ka muudel eesm&auml;rkidel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that credit and financial institutions refrain from carrying out transactions which they know or suspect to be related to money laundering until they have apprised the authorities referred to in Article 6. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad tagama, et enne selliste tehingute sooritamist, mille puhul on teada v&otilde;i on kahtlus, et need v&otilde;ivad olla seotud rahapesuga, teatavad krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused neist artiklis 6 osutatud asutustele. </eesti>
<inglise> Those authorities may, under conditions determined by their national legislation, give instructions not to execute the operation. </inglise>
<eesti> Need asutused v&otilde;ivad oma riigi vastavate &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt anda korralduse j&auml;tta tehing sooritamata. </eesti>
<inglise> Where such a transaction is suspected of giving rise to money laundering and where to refrain in such manner is impossible or is likely to frustrate efforts to pursue the beneficiaries of a suspected money-laundering operation, the institutions concerned shall apprise the authorities immediately afterwards. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui on kahtlus, et tehing v&otilde;ib olla seotud rahapesuga ning kui selle sooritamata j&auml;tmine ei ole v&otilde;imalik v&otilde;i v&otilde;ib takistada v&otilde;imalikust rahapesust tulusaajate tabamiseks tehtavaid j&otilde;upingutusi, teavitavad asjaomased asutused rahapesu t&otilde;kestamise eest vastutavaid asutusi kohe p&auml;rast tulusaajate tabamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> Credit and financial institutions and their directors and employees shall not disclose to the customer concerned nor to other third persons that information has been transmitted to the authorities in accordance with Articles 6 and 7 or that a money laundering investigation is being carried out. </inglise>
<eesti> Krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused ning nende juhid ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajad ei avalikusta asjaomasele kliendile v&otilde;i kolmandatele isikutele, et p&auml;devatele asutustele on esitatud andmeid vastavalt artiklitele 6 ja 7 v&otilde;i et rahapesuga seoses on algatatud uurimine. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> The disclosure in good faith to the authorities responsible for combating money laundering by an employee or director of a credit or financial institution of the information referred to in Articles 6 and 7 shall not constitute a breach of any restriction on disclosure of information imposed by contract or by any legislative, regulatory or administrative provision, and shall not involve the credit or financial institution, its directors or employees in liability of any kind. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui krediidi- v&otilde;i finantseerimisasutuse t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i juht edastab rahapesu t&otilde;kestamise eest vastutavatele p&auml;devatele asutustele artiklites 6 ja 7 osutatud teavet heauskselt, ei k&auml;sitata seda lepinguga v&otilde;i &otilde;igusnormidega teabe avalikustamisele kehtestatud piirangute rikkumisena ning krediidi- v&otilde;i finantseerimisasutus v&otilde;i tema juht ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajad ei kanna selle eest mingit vastutust. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that if, in the course of inspections carried out in credit or financial institutions by the competent authorities, or in any other way, those authorities discover facts that could constitute evidence of money laundering, they inform the authorities responsible for combating money laundering. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad tagama, et kui p&auml;devad asutused avastavad krediidi- v&otilde;i finantseerimisasutustes tehtavate inspekteerimiste k&auml;igus v&otilde;i m&otilde;nel muul viisil asjaolusid, mis v&otilde;ivad olla rahapesu t&otilde;endiks, teatavad nad sellest rahapesu t&otilde;kestamise eest vastutavatele asutustele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 11 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 11 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that credit and financial institutions: </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad tagama, et krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. establish adequate procedures of internal control and communication in order to forestall and prevent operations related to money laundering, </inglise>
<eesti> 1. kehtestavad asjakohase sisekontrolli ja sisese teavitamise korra rahapesuga seotud toimingute ennetamiseks ja t&otilde;kestamiseks, </eesti>
<inglise> 2. take appropriate measures so that their employees are aware of the provisions contained in this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. v&otilde;tavad asjakohased meetmed t&ouml;&ouml;tajate teavitamiseks k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tetest. </eesti>
<inglise> These measures shall include participation of their relevant employees in special training programmes to help them recognize operations which may be related to money laundering as well as to instruct them as to how to proceed in such cases. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende meetmete k&auml;igus saavad asjaomased t&ouml;&ouml;tajad eelk&otilde;ige osaleda spetsiaalsetes koolitusprogrammides, mille k&auml;igus &otilde;petatakse neid tuvastama v&otilde;imaliku rahapesuga seotud toiminguid ning antakse juhiseid sellistes olukordades tegutsemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 12 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 12 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that the provisions of this Directive are extended in whole or in part to professions and to categories of undertakings, other than the credit and financial institutions referred to in Article 1, which engage in activities which are particularly likely to be used for money-laundering purposes. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad tagama, et k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tteid laiendatakse osaliselt v&otilde;i t&auml;ielikult sellistele kutsealadele ja ettev&otilde;ttekategooriatele, kelle tegevust saab eriti t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt kasutada rahapesuks, v&auml;lja arvatud artiklis 1 osutatud krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutused. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 13 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 13 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A contact committee (hereinafter referred to as 'the Committee') shall be set up under the aegis of the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni juurde moodustatakse kontaktkomitee (edaspidi "komitee"). </eesti>
<inglise> Its function shall be: </inglise>
<eesti> Selle &uuml;lesanne on: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) without prejudice to Articles 169 and 170 of the Treaty, to facilitate harmonized implementation of this Directive through regular consultation on any practical problems arising from its application and on which exchanges of view are deemed useful; </inglise>
<eesti> a) h&otilde;lbustada, ilma et see piiraks asutamislepingu artiklite 169 ja 170 kohaldamist, k&auml;esoleva direktiivi koosk&otilde;lastatud rakendamist korrap&auml;raselt toimuvate konsultatsioonide abil kohaldamise k&auml;igus ilmnevais praktilistes probleemides, mille &uuml;le arvamuste vahetamist peetakse kasulikuks; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) to facilitate consultation between the Member States on the more stringent or additional conditions and obligations which they may lay down at national level; </inglise>
<eesti> b) h&otilde;lbustada liikmesriikide vahelisi konsultatsioone rangemate v&otilde;i t&auml;iendavate tingimuste ja kohustuste &uuml;le, mida nad v&otilde;ivad riigi tasandil ette n&auml;ha; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) to advise the Commission, if necessary, on any supplements or amendments to be made to this Directive or on any adjustments deemed necessary, in particular to harmonize the effects of Article 12; </inglise>
<eesti> c) vajaduse korral n&otilde;ustada komisjoni k&auml;esolevasse direktiivi tehtavate t&auml;ienduste v&otilde;i muudatuste asjus v&otilde;i kohanduste asjus, mida peetakse vajalikuks eelk&otilde;ige artikli 12 toime &uuml;htlustamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) to examine whether a profession or a category of undertaking should be included in the scope of Article 12 where it has been established that such profession or category of undertaking has been used in a Member State for money laundering. </inglise>
<eesti> d) teha kindlaks, kas kutseala v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tluskategooria peaks kuuluma artikli 12 reguleerimisalasse, kui selgub, et seda kutseala v&otilde;i kategooriat on teatavas liikmesriigis kasutatud rahapesu eesm&auml;rgil. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall not be the function of the Committee to appraise the merits of decisions taken by the competent authorities in individual cases. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee &uuml;lesannete hulka ei kuulu p&auml;devate asutuste poolt &uuml;ksikjuhtudel tehtud otsuste asjakohasuse hindamine. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The Committee shall be composed of persons appointed by the Member States and of representatives of the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee moodustatakse liikmesriikide poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud isikutest ja komisjoni esindajatest. </eesti>
<inglise> The secretariat shall be provided by the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Sekretariaaditeenuste eest hoolitseb komisjon. </eesti>
<inglise> The chairman shall be a representative of the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimees on komisjoni esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall be convened by its chairman, either on his own initiative or at the request of the delegation of a Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee koosolekud kutsub kokku komitee esimees kas omal algatusel v&otilde;i liikmesriigi delegatsiooni taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 14 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 14 </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State shall take appropriate measures to ensure full application of all the provisions of this Directive and shall in particular determine the penalties to be applied for infringement of the measures adopted pursuant to this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriik v&otilde;tab vastu asjakohased meetmed k&auml;esoleva direktiivi t&auml;ieliku kohaldamise tagamiseks ja m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaselt vastu v&otilde;etud meetmete rikkumise puhul kohaldatavad karistused. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 15 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 15 </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States may adopt or retain in force stricter provisions in the field covered by this Directive to prevent money laundering. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritud valdkonnas rahapesu t&otilde;kestamiseks vastu v&otilde;tta v&otilde;i kehtima j&auml;tta k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tetest rangemad s&auml;tted. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 16 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 16 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall bring into force the laws, regulations and administrative decisions necessary to comply with this Directive before 1 January 1993 at the latest. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid j&otilde;ustavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud &otilde;igusnormid hiljemalt 1. jaanuariks 1993. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where Member States adopt these measures, they shall contain a reference to this Directive or shall be accompanied by such reference on the occasion of their official publication. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigid need meetmed v&otilde;tavad, lisavad nad nendesse meetmetesse v&otilde;i nende meetmete ametliku avaldamise korral nende juurde viite k&auml;esolevale direktiivile. </eesti>
<inglise> The methods of making such a reference shall be laid down by the Member States. </inglise>
